##Start coding with highlight.js.

Syntax highlighting is now avalible on Slider. The libaray used is [highlightjs](https://highlightjs.org/). Highlightjs comes with 112 auto detected languages, 49 styles and is also capable of multi-language highlighting. Alternative themes are avaible, [Try the demos here](https://highlightjs.org/static/demo/). Your code never looked so good! Below shows an example of what can be done.

```
<!DOCTYPE html>  
<html>  
  <head>
    <style>
    body {
        background-color: #d0e4fe;
    }
    h1 {
        color: orange;
        text-align: center;
    }

    p {
        font-family: "arial";
        font-size: 20px;
    }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
      <h1>Hello World!</h1>
      <p id="demo">My first paragraph.</p>
      <button type="button" onclick="myFunction()">
          Click me.
      </button>
  </body>
</html>
```
